{"title_page": "Lincoln Zvasiya", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=May 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Lincoln Zvasiya\n|image          = \n|image_size     =\n|caption        = \n|fullname       = \n|birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1991|2|25|df=y}}\n|birth_place    = [[Harare]], Zimbabwe\n|height         = \n|position       = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n|currentclub    = [[CAPS United F.C.|CAPS United]]\n|clubnumber     = \n|youthyears1    = \n|youthclubs1    = Aces Youth Soccer Academy\n|years1         = \u20132011\n|clubs1         = [[Monomotapa United]]\n|caps1          = \n|goals1         = \n|years2         = 2011\n|clubs2         = [[FC Platinum]]\n|caps2          = \n|goals2         = \n|years3         = 2011\u20132014\n|clubs3         = [[Kaizer Chiefs F.C.|Kaizer Chiefs]]\n|caps3          = 25\n|goals3         = 1\n|clubs4         = \u2192 [[OFI Crete]] (loan)\n|years4         = 2013\u20132014\n|caps4          = 8\n|goals4         = 0\n|years5         = 2015\n|clubs5         = [[Harare City F.C.|Harare City]]\n|caps5          =\n|goals5         = \n|years6         = 2016\n|clubs6         = [[ZPC Kariba F.C.|ZPC Kariba]]\n|caps6          = \n|goals6         = \n|years7         = 2017\n|clubs7         = [[Dynamos F.C.|Dynamos Harare]]\n|caps7          = \n|goals7         = \n|years8         = 2018\n|clubs8         = [[Yadah Stars F.C.|Yadah Stars]]\n|caps8          = \n|goals8         = \n|years9         = 2019\u2013\n|clubs9         = [[CAPS United F.C.|CAPS United]]\n|caps9          = \n|goals9         = \n|nationalyears1 = 2011\u2013\n|nationalteam1  = [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]]\n|nationalcaps1  = 6\n|nationalgoals1 = 1\n|club-update    = 08:07, 2 July 2016 (UTC)\n|ntupdate       = 08:07, 2 July 2016 (UTC)\n}}\n\n'''Lincoln Zvasiya''' (born 25 February 1991) is a Zimbabwean professional [[association football|footballer]], who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[CAPS United F.C.|CAPS United]] and the [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe national team]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Club===\nBorn in [[Harare]], Zvasiya began his career with the [[Aces Youth Soccer Academy]]. After leaving Aces Youth he joined his first senior club when he signed for 2008 [[Zimbabwe Premier Soccer League]] winners [[Monomotapa United F.C.|Monomotapa United]].<ref name=\"Harare City 1\"/> After a year with Monomotapa, Zvasiya had a short stint with [[F.C. Platinum|Platinum]] before leaving them in the middle of 2013 to join South African club [[Kaizer Chiefs F.C.|Kaizer Chiefs]].<ref name=\"Soccerway\">{{cite news|title=Lincoln Zvasiya profile|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/lincoln-zvasiya/206758/|accessdate=2 July 2016|work=Soccerway|date=2 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nWith Kaizer Chiefs he won the [[2012\u201313 Premier Soccer League]] and the [[2012\u201313 Nedbank Cup]] before departing on loan to join Greek side [[OFI Crete F.C.|OFI Crete]] in July 2013.<ref name=\"RSSSF\">{{cite news|title=South Africa 2012/13|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesz/zaf2013.html|accessdate=2 July 2016|work=RSSSF|date=2 July 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"OFI Crete\">{{cite news|title=Kaizer Chiefs loan Lincoln Zvasiya to Greek club OFI Crete FC|url=http://www.kickoff.com/news/35488/kaizer-chiefs-loan-lincoln-zvasiya-to-greek-club-ofi-crete-fc|accessdate=2 July 2016|work=Kick Off|date=5 July 2013}}</ref> He returned to Kaizer Chiefs in December 2013 but was released nine months later.<ref name=\"Kaizer Chiefs 2\">{{cite news|title=Kaizer Chiefs finally release Lincoln Zvasiya|url=http://www.goal.com/en-za/news/4682/transfer-zone/2014/09/06/5087984/kaizer-chiefs-finally-release-lincoln-zvasiya|accessdate=2 July 2016|work=Goal|date=6 September 2014}}</ref> After spending September to December 2014 without a club, Zvasiya agreed to join [[Harare City F.C.|Harare City]] in 2015 but was released a few months later.<ref name=\"Harare City 1\">{{cite news|title=Lincoln Zvasiya joins Harare City|url=http://www.kickoff.com/news/51879/lincoln-zvasiya-joins-harare-city|accessdate=2 July 2016|work=Kick Off|date=15 January 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Harare City 2\">{{cite news|title=Zimbabwe: Harare City Offload Zvasiya|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201507220295.html|accessdate=2 July 2016|work=All Africa|date=22 July 2015}}</ref> In 2016, Zvasiya joined [[ZPC Kariba F.C.|ZPC Kariba]].<ref name=\"ZPC Kariba\">{{cite news|title=Silva remorseful|url=http://www.herald.co.zw/silva-regrets-scuffle/|accessdate=2 July 2016|work=Herald|date=27 February 2016}}</ref><ref>https://www.dailynews.co.zw/articles/2017/06/11/the-rise-fall-rise-of-zvasiya</ref>\n\n===International===\nZvasiya has won six caps and scored one goal for the [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe national team]], with his debut coming in a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] against [[Zambia national football team|Zambia]] in 2011.<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/> Three more appearances went past before he scored his first goal for his nation in a [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 CAF Second Round#Group G|2014 FIFA World Cup qualifying]] defeat to [[Egypt national football team|Egypt]].<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n\nIn October 2012, Zvasiya was cleared of  match fixing charges that came about from [[Asiagate]].<ref name=\"Asiagate\">{{cite news|title=Zimbabwe's Sadomba among seven cleared of match fixing|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/19828544|accessdate=2 July 2016|work=BBC|date=4 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===International===\n{{updated|2 July 2016}}.<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!National team!!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|[[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]]\n|2011||3||0\n|-\n|2012||0||0\n|-\n|2013||3||1\n|-\n|2014||0||0\n|-\n|2015||0||0\n|-\n|2016||0||0\n|-\n! colspan=2|Total!!6!!1\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n{{updated|2 July 2016}}. ''Scores and results list Zimbabwe's goal tally first.''<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n!Goal!!Date!!Venue!!Opponent!!Score!!Result!!Competition\n|-\n| 1 || 9 June 2013 || [[National Sports Stadium (Zimbabwe)|National Sports Stadium]], [[Harare]], [[Zimbabwe]] || {{fb|EGY}} || align=center | '''2'''\u20133 || align=center | 2\u20134 || [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 CAF Second Round#Group G|2014 FIFA World Cup qualification]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n;Kaizer Chiefs\n*[[Premier Soccer League]] (1): [[2012\u201313 Premier Soccer League|2012\u201313]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/><ref name=\"RSSSF\"/>\n*[[Nedbank Cup]] (1): [[2012\u201313 Nedbank Cup|2012\u201313]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/><ref name=\"RSSSF\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{FootballDatabase.eu|145926<!-- -lincoln-zvasiya -->}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zvasiya, Lincoln}}\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean footballers]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwe international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Monomotapa United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:F.C. Platinum players]]\n[[Category:Kaizer Chiefs F.C. players]]\n[[Category:OFI Crete F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Dynamos F.C. players]]\n[[Category:CAPS United players]]\n[[Category:Super League Greece players]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in South Africa]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean expatriate sportspeople in South Africa]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Greece]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean expatriate sportspeople in Greece]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Harare]]\n\n\n{{Zimbabwe-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=May 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Lincoln Zvasiya\n|image          = \n|image_size     =\n|caption        = \n|fullname       = \n|birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1991|2|25|df=y}}\n|birt